{"name": "pyterrier-t5", "metadata": {"name": "pyterrier-t5", "version": "0.1.0", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: Mozilla Public License 2.0 (MPL 2.0)", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python", "Topic :: Text Processing", "Topic :: Text Processing :: Indexing"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["python-terrier", "transformers", "torch", "sentencepiece"], "summary": "PyTerrier components for T5 ranking", "upload_time": 1732713831}, "documentation": ["# PyTerrier_t5\n\nThis is the [PyTerrier](https://github.com/terrier-org/pyterrier) plugin for the [Mono and Duo T5](https://arxiv.org/pdf/2101.05667.pdf) ranking approaches [[Nogueira21]](#Nogueira21).\n\nNote that this package only supports scoring from a pretrained models (like [this one](https://huggingface.co/castorini/monot5-base-msmarco)).\n\n## Installation\n\nThis repostory can be installed using Pip.\n\n    pip install --upgrade git+https://github.com/terrierteam/pyterrier_t5.git\n\n\n## Building T5 pipelines\n\nYou can use MonoT5 just like any other text-based re-ranker. By default, it uses a MonoT5 model previously\ntrained on MS MARCO passage ranking training queries.\n\n```python\nimport pyterrier as pt\nfrom pyterrier_t5 import MonoT5ReRanker, DuoT5ReRanker\nmonoT5 = MonoT5ReRanker() # loads castorini/monot5-base-msmarco by default\nduoT5 = DuoT5ReRanker() # loads castorini/duot5-base-msmarco by default\n\ndataset = pt.get_dataset(\"irds:vaswani\")\nbm25 = pt.BatchRetrieve(pt.get_dataset(\"vaswani\").get_index(), wmodel=\"BM25\")\nmono_pipeline = bm25 >> pt.text.get_text(dataset, \"text\") >> monoT5\nduo_pipeline = mono_pipeline % 5 >> duoT5 # apply a rank cutoff of 5 from monoT5 since duoT5 is too costly to run over the full result list\n```\n\nNote that both approaches require the document text to be included in the dataframe (see [pt.text.get_text](https://pyterrier.readthedocs.io/en/latest/text.html#pyterrier.text.get_text)).\n\nMonoT5ReRanker and DuoT5ReRanker have the following options:\n - `model` (default: `'castorini/monot5-base-msmarco'` for mono, `'castorini/duot5-base-msmarco'` for duo). HGF model name. Defaults to a version trained on MS MARCO passage ranking.\n - `tok_model` (default: `'t5-base'`). HGF tokenizer name.\n - `batch_size` (default: `4`). How many documents to process at the same time.\n - `text_field` (default: `text`). The dataframe attribute in which the document text is stored.\n - `verbose` (default: `True`). Show progress bar.\n\n## Examples\n\nCheckout out the notebooks, even on Colab:\n\n - Reranking a dataframe [[Github](https://github.com/terrierteam/pyterrier_t5/blob/master/pyterrier_monoT5_direct_rerank.ipynb)] [[Colab](https://colab.research.google.com/github/terrierteam/pyterrier_t5/blob/master/pyterrier_monoT5_direct_rerank.ipynb)]\n - Vaswani [[Github](https://github.com/terrierteam/pyterrier_t5/blob/master/pyterrier_t5_vaswani.ipynb)] [[Colab](https://colab.research.google.com/github/terrierteam/pyterrier_t5/blob/master/pyterrier_t5_vaswani.ipynb)]\n - TREC-COVID [[Github](https://github.com/terrierteam/pyterrier_t5/blob/master/pyterrier_t5_trec-covid.ipynb)] [[Colab](https://colab.research.google.com/github/terrierteam/pyterrier_t5/blob/master/pyterrier_t5_trec-covid.ipynb)]\n\n## Implementation Details\n\nWe use a PyTerrier transformer to score documents using a T5 model.\n\nSequences longer than the model's maximum of 512 tokens are silently truncated. Consider splitting long texts\ninto passages and aggregating the results ([examples](https://pyterrier.readthedocs.io/en/latest/text.html#working-with-passages-rather-than-documents)).\n\n## References\n\n  - <a id=\"Nogueira21\"/>Ronak Pradeep, Rodrigo Nogueira, and Jimmy Lin. The Expando-Mono-Duo Design Pattern for Text Ranking withPretrained Sequence-to-Sequence Models. https://arxiv.org/pdf/2101.05667.pdf\n  - <a id=\"Macdonald20\"/>Craig Macdonald, Nicola Tonellotto. Declarative Experimentation inInformation Retrieval using PyTerrier. Craig Macdonald and Nicola Tonellotto. In Proceedings of ICTIR 2020. https://arxiv.org/abs/2007.14271\n\n## Credits\n\n- Sean MacAvaney, University of Glasgow\n"], "modules": [{"name": "training.monot5.t5train", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "training.monot5.t5train.iter_train_samples", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5train.build_validation_data", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "training.monot5.t5train.BATCH_SIZE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5train._logger", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5train.OUTPUTS", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5train.train_iter", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5train.model", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5train.tokenizer", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5train.optimizer", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5train.reranker", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5train.reranker.REL", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5train.reranker.NREL", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5train.valid_data", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5train.valid_qrels", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5train.epoch", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5train.max_ndcg", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5train.total_loss", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5train.count", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5train.inp_ids", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5train.out_ids", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5train.loss", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5train.total_loss", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5train.reranker.model", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5train.reranker.verbose", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5train.res", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5train.reranker.verbose", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5train.metrics", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5train.max_ndcg", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5-train-bm25negs", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "training.monot5.t5-train-bm25negs.iter_train", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "training.monot5.t5-train-bm25negs.parser", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5-train-bm25negs.args", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5-train-bm25negs.rng", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5-train-bm25negs._logger", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5-train-bm25negs.bm25", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5-train-bm25negs.OUTPUTS", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5-train-bm25negs.train_iter", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5-train-bm25negs.model", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5-train-bm25negs.tokenizer", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5-train-bm25negs.optimizer", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5-train-bm25negs.OUT_IDS", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "training.monot5.t5-train-bm25negs